The '''Arab American Association of New York''' is an [[Arab Americans|Arab American]] and [[Muslim]] civil rights organization located in [[New York (state)|New York]].<ref name="washingtonpost">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/ive-never-seen-that-before-activists-marvel-as-calls-for-immigrant-rights-enter-the-mainstream/2018/07/06/9dab53f0-812f-11e8-b9a5-7e1c013f8c33_story.html|website=washingtonpost.com|title=The Washington Post|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref><ref name="documentedny">{{cite web|url=https://documentedny.com/2018/07/09/bitta-mostofi-on-immigration-in-nyc/|title=Bitta Mostofi on Immigration in NYC|website=Documented|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref><ref name="brooklyndaily">{{cite web|url=https://www.brooklyndaily.com/stories/2018/29/br-arab-american-bazaar-2018-07-20-bk.html|website=brooklyndaily.com|title=Locals celebrate Middle Eastern culture at Ridge&#8217;s annual Arab American Bazaar &#8226; Brooklyn Daily|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref><ref name="papermag">{{cite web|url=http://www.papermag.com/july-4th-fourth-of-july-2583622679.html|website=papermag.com|title=13 American Cultural Leaders on What July 4th Means to Them|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref><ref name="brooklynreporter">{{cite web|url=https://brooklynreporter.com/story/rock-the-block-street-fair-bay-ridge/|website=Brooklynreporter.com|title=Rock the Block” street fair in Bay Ridge highlights health|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref><ref name="gothamist">{{cite web|url=http://gothamist.com/2018/07/01/immigration_keep_families_together_nyc_march_photos.php#photo-1|website=gothamist.com|title=Photos: Thousands Turn Out For 'Keep Families Together' March: Gothamist|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref><ref name="brooklynreporter2">{{cite web|url=https://brooklynreporter.com/story/arab-americans-celebrate-heritage-12th-annual-bazaar-bay-ridge/|website=Brooklynreporter.com|title=Arab-Americans celebrate their heritage at 12th annual Bazaar in Bay Ridge|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref><ref name="haaretz">{{cite web|url=https://www.haaretz.com/us-news/.premium-jews-and-muslims-unite-in-new-york-to-protest-trump-s-travel-ban-1.6218512|title=Jews and Muslims unite in New York to protest Trump's travel ban - U.S. News|website=Haaretz.com|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref><ref name="documentedny2">{{cite web|url=https://documentedny.com/2018/06/22/the-high-cost-of-the-travel-ban-yemenis-pay-thousands-to-reunite-families/|website=documentedny.com|title=The High Cost of the Travel Ban: Yemenis pay Thousands to Reunite Families|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref>
[[Linda Sarsour]] was the former executive director of the organization until stepping down from the position in 2017.<ref name="nytimes">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/09/nyregion/linda-sarsour-is-a-brooklyn-homegirl-in-a-hijab.html|title=Linda Sarsour Is a Brooklyn Homegirl in a Hijab|website=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref><ref name="voicesofny">{{cite web|url=https://voicesofny.org/2017/02/linda-sarsour-leaving-arab-american-association/|website=voicesofny.org|title=Linda Sarsour Leaving Arab American Association|accessdate=2018-07-20}}</ref>
